            <title>[SUREFIRE-1701] Surefire / Failsafe rerun failed tests functionality fails with JUnit 5 if using @DisplayName</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1701</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using the &lt;tt&gt;@DisplayName&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;annotation in JUnit Jupiter prevents &lt;tt&gt;rerunFailedTestsCount&lt;/tt&gt; functionality in surefire and failsafe from working. Example of this can be found &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/quiram/surefire-retry-failed-tests-issue&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt;&#160;it is possible that other annotations make this functionality fail too, but I haven&apos;t checked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
